        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 2:50PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Clayton, or near Dillard, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clayton, Mountain City, Tiger, Dillard, Black Rock Mountain State
Park, Lakemont, Sky Valley, and Lake Rabun.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
